LAGOS â€“ The Vice-Chancellor, Lagos State University (LASU), Prof. Olanrewaju Fagbohun (SAN), has approved the appointment of Prof. Abiodun Adewuya as the Acting Provost, Lagos State University College of Medicine (LASUCOM). Prof. Adewuya, a Professor of Mental Health, resumed as Provost of the College on December 27, 2019, taking over from Prof. Anthonia Ogbera. The VC, in a statement issued by Ademola Adekoya, Coordinator, Centre for Information, Press and Public Relations, LASU, expressed appreciation to the immediate-past Acting Provost, Prof. Anthonia Ogbera, for her leadership and selfless service during her tenure as Acting Provost of the College. He praised her for the laudable achievements and development strides recorded by the college during her tenure and charged the new Acting Provost to continue from where she stopped. He prayed that God would continue to strengthen the former Acting Provost as she carries on with other assignments in the college. Adewuya is a Professor of Psychiatry at the Lagos State University College of Medicine (LASUCOM) and an Honorary Consultant Psychiatrist at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital (LASUTH). He had his medical school (MBChB) training at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, where he also had his postgraduate residency training in psychiatry and became a Fellow of the Faculty of Psychiatry of both the West African College of Physician (FWACP) and the National Postgraduate Medical College of Physician (FMCPsych). He has over 60 academic publications in indexed journals and an editorial board member of four international journals of psychiatry. He is a Research Fellow at the Institute of Psychiatry (IOP), Kings College, London. His research interests include Global Mental Health, Women Mental Health, Social Psychiatry and Primary Care Mental Health.